<tal:macro xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
           xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
           metal:use-macro="view.base_template">

<tal:slot metal:fill-slot="content">
<section id="main-content">

    <p class="text-justified">
        There is a wide variety of current applications and libraries
        for different audiences. The following list does not claim to
        be complete and specifically does not call out applications
        merely using this service.
    </p>

    <h3>Mozilla Stumbler for Android</h3>

    <div class="app-callout-left text-justified">
        <p >
            Mozilla Stumbler is an open source Android application, which both
            collects data to contribute to the service and also includes a
            test mode to show ones location on a map.
        </p>

        <p>
            You can find <a href="https://github.com/mozilla/MozStumbler">
                Mozilla Stumbler on Github</a>
            to download it or to contribute to its development.
        </p>

        <p>
            As an alternative you can also
            <a href="https://f-droid.org/wiki/page/org.mozilla.mozstumbler">
                install Mozilla Stumbler from the f-droid catalog</a>.
        </p>

        <p>
            Mozilla Stumbler allows you to compete in our
            <a href="/leaders">leaderboards</a> by choosing a nickname
            in its preferences screen.
        </p>

    </div>

    <div class="app-callout-right">
        <a href="https://github.com/mozilla/MozStumbler">
            <img src="/static/images/mozstumbler.png"
                 title="Mozilla Stumbler on Github"
                 width="144" height="256" /></a>
    </div>

    <h3 class="separator">Firefox for Android</h3>

    <p class="text-justified">
        Nightly versions of
        <a href="https://quality.mozilla.org/docs/mobile-firefox/how-to-install-fennec-nightly-builds/">Firefox for Android</a>
        include a way to contribute data and enhance this service. In order
        to enable this, you need to go to the Mozilla settings section and
        look for the contribution option under data choices.
    </p>

    <h3>Firefox OS</h3>

    <p class="text-justified">
        Integration of this service into Firefox OS is an ongoing process.
        If the specific Firefox OS device uses this service depends on a
        number of factors including which chipset is used in the device,
        which manufacturer built the device and via what partner and channel
        it was sold or given out.
    </p>

    <p class="text-justified">
        In general client side code to talk to this service appeared in
        Firefox OS version 1.3T and 1.4.
    </p>

    <h3>FxStumbler</h3>

    <p class="text-justified">
        FxStumbler is an open source Firefox OS application similar in purpose
        to Mozilla Stumbler. It collects data about the radio environment to
        enhance the service. To contribute to the development of
        <a href="https://github.com/clochix/FxStumbler">
            FxStumbler visit it on github</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Firefox Desktop</h3>

    <p class="text-justified">
        Recent versions of Firefox Desktop allow you to use this service
        instead of the default location provider. Please refer to the
        documentation on
        <a href="https://mozilla-ichnaea.readthedocs.org/en/latest/usage.html#firefox-desktop">
            how to customize the location provider</a> in our development
        documentation.
    </p>

</section>
</tal:slot>

</tal:macro>
